x4freetext: Inelastic scattering of fast neutrons from au-197.
3MeV Van de Graaff with terminal pulsing, pulse
metal target on ta backing, thickness 5-15 keV. When
second neutron group from Li interfered a target of H-3
absorbed in Ti and 30 keV thick was used.
Metal-  hollow right cylinder of metal and dimensions
Time of flight with 5 nanosec overall resolution
Plastic scintillator of 10cm diam and 2.5 cm
thick, for low energy neutrons a 1cm thick scintillator
Long counter as flux monitor at 0 degrees
Detector at 90 degrees to neutron beam with flux
monitor(long counter) on axis of beam
cross-section of C as published in ANL-5567(Rev)1961
was used as normalization for the detector efficiency
For flux attenuation and multiple scattering, total
Errors given in table are due to statistics only
systematic errors due to carbon cross-section used or
from relative long counter efficiency could total
Angular distribution isotropic within 10 percent error
Spin-parity values were assigned to the energy
levels determined in experiment using Hauser-Feshbach
